{
  "texts": [
    "We refer readers to the supplementary for more details and visualization on the trajectory of scaletravel.",
    "The full latent refinement technique is shown in Fig. 3 and can be written as Algorithm 1 Multi-Scale Encoding Params:Latent Z, Scales s 1:K def MultiScaleEnc(Z, s 1:K) R ← [] for k = 1, 2,..., K do r k ← Q(down(Z -Z k-1, s k)) R.append(r k) Z k ← k i=1 up(r i, s K) return R = r 1:K Algorithm 2 Scale-Travel Params:Latent Z l, Scales s 1:m, Target m def ScaleTravel(Z l, s 1:m, m) R ← [] for k = 1, 2,..., m do r k ← Q(down(Z l -Z k-1, s k)) R.append(r k) Z k ← k i=1 up(r i, s K) return R = r 1:m ResultsIn this section, we present the experiment results of our DIVERSEVAR, comparing both diversity and quality with existing diversity enhancement techniques on VARs.",
    "Evaluation SetupVAR Models.",
    "For text-conditioned VAR models, we use Infinity [21] and Switti [66].",
    "Infinity trains a bitwise transformer for scaling the vocabulary to infinite size, and Switti improves the efficiency and scalability of VAR [61] by solving training instability and using non-causal self-attention for faster sampling.Benchmarks and Evaluation Metrics."
  ]
}